Once upon a time, a woodcutter lived near a river. One day, while cutting wood, his axe fell into the river.
The woodcutter became very sad because it was his only axe. Suddenly, a fairy appeared and offered to help. She dived into the river and brought out a golden axe.
"Is this your axe?" she asked.
"No," said the woodcutter honestly.
The fairy then brought out a silver axe.
"Is this yours?"
Again, the woodcutter said, "No."
Finally, she brought out his old iron axe.
"Yes, that's my axe!" he replied happily.
The fairy was pleased with his honesty and rewarded him with all three axes.
Moral: Honesty is the best policy.
